[{"id":"VR876708","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of light, represented by equally spaced vertical lines, moving horizontally to the right towards a vertical double slit. Three smaller waves are shown to the right of the slits, each represented by a series of equally spaced lines. The central wave moves horizontally to the right. The upper wave moves upward and to the right at an angle theta above the horizontal. The lower wave moves downward and to the right at an angle theta below the horizontal. A notes states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR876708.g06.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Light of frequency <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f\"><math alttext=\"f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>f</mi></math></span></span> having planar wave fronts are incident on a double slit, as shown in the figure. Beyond the slits, the light is found to travel in three directions. Some of the light travels in the same direction as the original light. Other parts of the light are traveling in directions that are an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> from the original direction, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> is NOT a small angle. What is the distance between the centers of the slits?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR876708_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f over theta\"><math alttext=\"f over theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mi>θ</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction c over f theta, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction c over f theta, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mrow><mi>f</mi><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f over sine of theta\"><math alttext=\"f over sine of theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction c over f sine of theta, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction c over f sine of theta, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mrow><mi>f</mi><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>sin</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]